<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="92218CE2-A543-5AE3-99D4-8AD12DF2E7A9" authority="Ye, 1981" authorityName="Ye" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga (Pterosarcophaga)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pterosarcophaga">Sarcophaga Pterosarcophaga Ye, 1981</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pterosarcophaga</taxonomicName>
Ye, 1981: 229. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ye &amp; Ni" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga emeishanensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeishanensis">Pterosarcophaga emeishanensis</taxonomicName>
Ye &amp; Ni, 1981, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosacophaga" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosacophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">Pterosacophaga</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B47" refString="Ye, ZM, 1981. [Description of Pterosarcophaga.] In: Ye ZM, Ni T, Liu ZJ (Eds) Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of the tribe Sarcophagini (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zoological Research 2: 229." title="[Description of Pterosarcophaga.] In: Ye ZM, Ni T, Liu ZJ (Eds) Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of the tribe Sarcophagini (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zoological Research 2: 229." year="1981">Ye 1981</bibRefCitation>
: 230. Incorrect original spelling of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pterosarcophaga</taxonomicName>
, by First Reviser action of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B48" refString="Ye, ZM, 1982. The checklist of Chinese Sarcophaginae. China Academic Journal Electronic Publishing House 11-23." title="The checklist of Chinese Sarcophaginae. China Academic Journal Electronic Publishing House 11 - 23." year="1982">Ye (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Magnicauda</taxonomicName>
Wei, 2005: 405. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda linjiangensis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linjiangensis">Magnicauda linjiangensis</taxonomicName>
Wei, 2005, by original designation. Syn. nov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Maginicauda" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maginicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">Maginicauda</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 409. Incorrect original spelling of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Magnicauda</taxonomicName>
, by First Reviser action in the present paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Monotypic subgenera in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">sensu lato</emphasis>
) are often erected for lack of evidence as to their phylogenetic relationships, and as such they convey little if any information. We prefer a classification based on similarities rather than on differences, and as 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei (2005)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Magnicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pterosarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the male cerci of the type species of both subgenera being expanded, wing-like, in lateral view, we are here treating the two nominal subgenera as synonyms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
Ye in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B49" refString="Ye, ZM, Ni, T, 1981. [Description of Pterosarcophaga emeishanensis.] In: Ye ZM, Ni T, Liu ZJ (Eds) Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of the tribe Sarcophagini (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zoological Research 2: 229." title="[Description of Pterosarcophaga emeishanensis.] In: Ye ZM, Ni T, Liu ZJ (Eds) Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of the tribe Sarcophagini (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Zoological Research 2: 229." year="1981">Ye and Ni (1981)</bibRefCitation>
provided two different spellings: &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pterosarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (pp. 229, 232, 233) and &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosacophaga" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosacophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pterosacophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (p. 230). By using only the spelling &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pterosarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterosarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pterosarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ye, ZM" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B48" refString="Ye, ZM, 1982. The checklist of Chinese Sarcophaginae. China Academic Journal Electronic Publishing House 11-23." title="The checklist of Chinese Sarcophaginae. China Academic Journal Electronic Publishing House 11 - 23." year="1982">Ye (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 21) acted as First Reviser according to Article 24.2.4 of the Code.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei (2005)</bibRefCitation>
provided two different spellings: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Magnicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (pp. 404-406, 408) and &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Maginicauda" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maginicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Maginicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (p. 409). Since then, the only mention of this genus-group name we have found is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B36" refString="Verves, YuG, 2020. An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera). Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 1: 1 - 68" title="An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera)." volume="1" year="2020">Verves (2020</bibRefCitation>
: 48); however, as only the spelling &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Maginicauda" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maginicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Maginicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; was used, the criteria of Article 24.2.3 for a First Reviser action were not fulfilled. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Jin, DC" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="404 - 409" refId="B40" refString="Wei, LM, 2005. Sarcophagidae. In: Jin, DC, Li, ZZ, Eds., Insects from Xishui Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 404 - 409" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Xishui Landscape." year="2005">Wei (2005)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide an explicit etymology, but the description of a remarkably broad male cercus is here taken to indicate that &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Magnicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; was the intended spelling. This is supported by the repeated use of this spelling, whereas the spelling &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Maginicauda" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maginicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Maginicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; was used only once. We herewith select &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Magnicauda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magnicauda" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Magnicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; to be the correct original spelling, by First Reviser action.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
